summary:
Energy is essential for human progress and I want to contribute to the challenge of cutting off CO2 emissions caused by the use of fossil fuels. To contribute to this challenge, I focussed my education on the energy sector, from technologies to economic and societal effects. I am specialized in biomass, hydrogen and fuel cell systems, but my interest goes beyond energy, and I am concerned about the sustainability of the agriculture, industry and transport sectors, from resources availability to waste management.

In the past years, I have

- Defined and implemented research questions;
- Carried out modelling and experiments on sustainable energy systems;
- Collected, analysed, synthesised data and presented results; 
- Led multicultural teams and coordinated multidisciplinary projects;
- Defined projects objectives and implementation steps;
- Monitored project budget and progress;
- Managed the communication with projects partners and stakeholders.

I am results-oriented, proactive and I have an organized and analytical approach, alongside strong  communication skills. During the past years, I realized I perform best in environments where I can cooperate, motivate, and connect people, and where I can successfully organize and follow projects from the beginning to the on-schedule and on-budget completion. I get excited by transforming obstacles into opportunities and I am energized by making team projects successful.

I want to use my technical background next to my interpersonal skills and creativity to set-up and deliver projects to accelerate society transition towards a more sustainable future.

profile_positions.description:
Scientific and technical research, knowledge management, analysis and studies of critical materials and associated value chains for low carbon technologies.

Main activities:
- Conduct analysis of supply and demand for raw and processed materials of low-carbon technologies;
- Assess opportunities and threats of the European energy-technology component-manufacturing and technology-development industry;
- Identify solutions to overcome supply chain bottlenecks;
- Provide ad-hoc support to EU policy officers on cross-cutting issues for critical raw materials, processed materials and associated manufacturing routes;
- Follow-up the developments in EU's policies that relate with its industrial strategy and a clean energy tech leadership vision in the context of the transition to climate neutrality;
- Draft comprehensive analysis reports and / or updates to existing ones on materials issues in view of EU Industrial strategy and Green Deal;
- Write policy briefs and scientific papers for peer-review publications;
- Map low-carbon energy-technology value chains through the collection, validation and consolidation of data.

Help clients achieve their innovation goals within the Energy & Environment sector by using sector and subsidy landscape knowledge, creativity and communication skills.

Main activities:
- Assessed opportunities to accelerate clients innovation in the hydrogen, wind and industrial decarbonisation sectors;
- Drafted high quality project plans, reports and funding applications;
- Outlined a methodology to determine and increase the replication potential of innovative technologies in the biomass conversion sector;
- Analysed on-going and future projects in the hydrogen sector to assess competition and chances of tendering success;
- Maintained a clear and effective communication flow with clients and colleagues.

Main activities:
- Supervised PhDs and researchers in the field of biomass, fuel cells and electrolysis;
- Collaborated to engineering a fuel cell system for industrial applications;
- Contributed to the development of a new inter-faculty research programme on Negative Emissions.

HORIZON2020 project FlexiFuel-SOFC

Topic: Development of an innovative, highly efficient and fuel-flexible micro-scale biomass fuel cell combined heat and power system

Main activities:
- Coordinated TU Delft activities;
- Led and worked the TU Delft team (10+ people among students, post-graduates, support staff and technicians);
- Managed the communication with internal and external stakeholders, among which team members, project partners, European Commission, and equipment suppliers;
- Followed the development of a new energy technology from lab-scale design to test-plant operation; 
- Independently designed and implemented research activities;
- Designed (PFD, P&ID and equipment specification) and commissioned new test-rigs;
- Performed experiments on biomass gasification, fuel cells and syngas treatment systems;
- Modelled a microCHP system in Cycle Tempo, Aspen and FactSage and identified strategies to increase efficiency and reduce system complexity;
- Collected, analysed, and summarised data and knowledge gained;
- Supervised and advised 8 MSc students in their graduation projects;
- Collaborated with other researchers to solve problems and design new research lines;
- Presented scientific results in international conferences with oral and poster presentations and published in peer-reviewed journals;
- Efficiently reported project outcomes with deliverables and presented to external stakeholders in review meetings and project workshops;
- Learnt about technology market studies, techno-economic and energy policy analysis, and impact assessment.

FP7 project KnowHy

Topic: Building and Providing an on-line course with hand-on sessions on Fuel Cells & Hydrogen technologies specifically designed for technicians and workers 

Main activities:
- Planned, defined and managed the project objectives, the implementation steps, and the risks;
- Coordinated and monitored the project timely progress, budget and quality;
- Led the TU Delft team and the project consortium;
- Managed the communication with external stakeholders and among projects partners (13 organizations);
- Reported outcomes to European Commission with deliverables and detailed implementation roadmap towards planned milestones;
- Performed a market analysis to identify course stakeholders, target group and applications;
- Developed the course material, designed hands-on sessions and offered the course;
- Organized and conducted a project workshop to attract and engage clients and stakeholders.


Activities in other projects:
- Wrote EU Proposals (accepted and funded) on hydrogen & fuel cells technologies and on innovative sanitation systems;
- Performed research and dissemination activities, and administrative tasks for the human-waste-based power plants developed by TU Delft within the “Reinvent the toilet challenge” funded by The Bill & Melinda Gates foundation;
- Analyzed and compared CAPEX and OPEX of hydrogen production systems from renewable electricity and performed experiments on H2O and CO2 electrolysis.

volunteer_experiences.description:
- Provide advice to MSc, PDEngs and PhD students on their Curriculum Vitae and Motivation Letter;
- Refine active listening skills;
- Improve my positive and communicative attitude;
- Trained on giving and receiving feedback.

Delft Women in Science is the network for female scientists within the Delft University of Technology. Established in 2006, DEWIS has 650 female scientists as members. As an active member, I have contributed to the involvement of young researchers in the society, helped shaping the initiative and promoted a diverse environment at TU Delft.

I have gained knowledge on:
- Importance of diversity for science, education and the whole society;
- seen and unseen behavioural issues (bias awareness);
- power and the misuse of power;
- how to create a pleasant and safe workplace for everyone;
- tools to deal with poor behavior in the work environment (active bystander).

- Designed an On-Site Electrolytic Chlorinator (OSEC) system for the cost-effective and eco-friendly production of a disinfectant solution of sodium hypochlorite in rural communities;
- Devised a financial strategy for a Guatemalan agricultural cooperative to pay-back the system costs;
- Raised the funds necessary for the execution of the project;
- Installed and commissioned the system;
- Trained the local personnel;
- Monitored the system performances and designed a solution to enable constant remote monitoring;
- Planned, monitored and kept the project on schedule and on budget.
